        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 6:31PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Sweetwater Creek State
Park, or near Douglasville. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sweetwater Creek State Park, Six Flags Over Georgia, Lithia Springs,
Austell, Mableton, Douglasville, Powder Springs, Smyrna, and City of
South Fulton.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
